# Belt-and-suspenders: keep private/local files out of the build context so a
# future `COPY . .` can never bake them into an image. The current Dockerfile
# uses selective `COPY chronicle/ … java-server/ …` (never `COPY . .`), and the
# build regenerates node_modules via `npm ci`, so none of these break the build.
docs/
decision-doc.md
# only local/secret env files — NOT committed build inputs like chronicle/.env.production
**/.env*.local
.git
node_modules
